#DatasetTask#: Predict whether the patient has diabetes. Yes or no?
Glucose: Plasma glucose concentration a 2 hours in an oral glucose tolerance test
BMI: Body mass index (weight in kg/(height in m)^2)
PregnanciesLessEqual2: Number of times pregnant is 2 or fewer
GlucoseLessEqual125: Plasma glucose concentration is 125 mg/dL or lower
BloodPressureLessEqual80: Diastolic blood pressure is 80 mm Hg or lower
SkinThicknessLessEqual20: Triceps skin fold thickness is 20 mm or less
InsulinLessEqual100: Hour serum insulin is 100 mu U/ml or lower
BMILessEqual30: Body mass index is 30 or lower
DiabetesPedigreeFunctionLessEqual0.5: Diabetes pedigree function is 0.5 or lower
GlucoseInRange70-125: Plasma glucose concentration is between 70 and 125 mg/dL
BMIInRange18.5-30: Body mass index is between 18.5 and 30
PregnanciesGreaterEqual3: Number of times pregnant is 3 or more
GlucoseGreater125: Plasma glucose concentration is greater than 125 mg/dL
BloodPressureGreaterEqual80: Diastolic blood pressure is 80 mm Hg or higher
SkinThicknessGreater25: Triceps skin fold thickness is greater than 25 mm
InsulinGreater100: Hour serum insulin is greater than 100 mu U/ml
BMIGreater30: Body mass index is greater than 30
DiabetesPedigreeFunctionGreater0.5: Diabetes pedigree function is greater than 0.5
GlucoseInRange126-200: Plasma glucose concentration is between 126 and 200 mg/dL
BMIInRange30-40: Body mass index is between 30 and 40
